[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzing test using the ExpanderFuzzer has triggered an Out of Memory [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOOM[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m error [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the Apache Commons Compress library. The issue occurs during the decompression [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata using the Z compression format [0m[1;39m([0m[39mLZW algorithm[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The fuzzer detected this as a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity issue [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFuzzerSecurityIssueLow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a reproducible crash.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Overview[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing harness ExpanderFuzzer, which tests the Apache Commons Compress [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibrary's `Expander` class, has encountered a Java heap space exhaustion error. The[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer was configured to run with libFuzzer engine in interactive mode with [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations on a test case when the failure occurred.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Classification[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis issue has been classified as a **Denial of Service [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability** [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough resource exhaustion. The fuzzer's security detection system categorized it [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas `FuzzerSecurityIssueLow`, indicating it poses a security concern but may not be [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritically severe. The root cause is an `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Stack Trace Analysis[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe exception originates from the following call chain:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Entry Point**: `[0m[1;35mExpanderFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - The fuzzing harness [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry point[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Expander Operations**: [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mExpander.expand[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - High-level expansion method[0m                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Compression Factory**: `[0m[1;35mCompressorStreamFactory.createCompressorInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Z Compressor Initialization**: `ZCompressorInputStream.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - Constructor[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor Z format decompressor[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **LZW Stream Initialization**: [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mLZWInputStream.initializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - Method called recursively[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is where the memory allocation failure occurs at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m and propagates [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough recursive call at line [0m[1;36m220[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Recursive Table Initialization**: The stack trace shows [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mLZWInputStream.initializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` being called recursively [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m calling line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, suggesting the initialization process may be attempting to allocate tables [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbased on input-controlled parameters.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Memory Configuration**: The error message suggests using `-Xmx1710m` to [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreproduce the issue, indicating the fuzzer was running with limited heap space [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maround [0m[1;36m1.[0m[39m7GB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when the failure occurred.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Input-Driven Memory Allocation**: The fact that this can be triggered by [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer-generated input suggests that the table initialization in the LZW [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecompression logic may be allocating memory based on values read from the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompressed input without proper validation or bounds checking.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Compression Format**: The issue specifically occurs with the Z compression [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUnix compress format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which uses the LZW algorithm.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Missing Input Validation in ZCompressorInputStream**: The constructor reads [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`maxCodeSize` from the untrusted input file [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m75[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and passes it directly to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35minitializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without validating it's within safe bounds [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Inadequate Bounds Checking in [0m[1;35mLZWInputStream.initializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The single-argument version [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m178[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m only checks if `[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m << maxCodeSize < [0m[1;36m256[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlower bound ~[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, relying on integer overflow as a side effect for upper bound[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No explicit upper bound validation exists[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For `maxCodeSize = [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m`, it attempts to allocate ~[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m GB [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m073[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m741[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m824[0m[39m entries ×[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m bytes/entry[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Integer Overflow in Memory Limit Calculation**: [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m211[0m[39m: `int maxTableSize = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m << maxCodeSize` overflows to negative for [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`maxCodeSize >= [0m[1;36m31[0m[39m`[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens before the cast to long at line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m, making the [0m[32m"account [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mfor potential overflow"[0m[39m comment ineffective[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Negative memory calculations bypass the memory limit check at line [0m[1;36m216[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **No Default Memory Limit in Singleton Factory**:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The singleton instance uses the default constructor setting `memoryLimitInKb =[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m-1[0m[39m`[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Expander class uses this singleton, completely bypassing memory checks[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test cases pass because they explicitly set a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m MB memory limit, but [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproduction code paths don't[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Critical Code Locations[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Vulnerable Path:**[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExpanderFuzzer → [0m[1;35mExpander.decompress[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → [0m[1;35mCompressorStreamFactory.getSingleton[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ [0m[1;35mcreateCompressorInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[33mmemoryLimitInKb[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ [0m[1;35mZCompressorInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39min, [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ [0m[1;35minitializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[33mmaxCodeSize[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mskips memory check[0m[1;39m][0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ allocates ~[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m GB → OutOfMemoryError[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix: Add Input Validation in ZCompressorInputStream[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/compressors/z/ZCompressorInputStream.jav[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma`[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Action:** Add explicit validation in the constructor after line [0m[1;36m82[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaxCodeSize is extracted[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and before line [0m[1;36m86[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere initializeTables is called[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After line [0m[1;36m82[0m[39m: maxCodeSize = thirdByte & MAX_CODE_SIZE_MASK;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Add validation:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxCodeSize < [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m || maxCodeSize > [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid maxCodeSize of "[0m[39m + maxCodeSize + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[32m". Values must be in the range [0m[32m[[0m[32m9, 30[0m[32m][0m[32m."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale:**[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The test at `[0m[1;35mZCompressorInputStreamTest.testInvalidMaxCodeSize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` expects [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IllegalArgumentException` for values < [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m and >= [0m[1;36m31[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Valid range should be [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m to match DEFAULT_CODE_SIZE [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m9[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and prevent [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessive allocation[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This validation occurs regardless of memory limit settings, protecting all code [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents integer overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxCodeSize >= [0m[1;36m31[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and excessive allocation [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mmaxCodeSize = [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Aligns with the test expectations and Z format practical limits[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Secondary Fix: Improve Memory Limit Calculation in LZWInputStream[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/compressors/lzw/LZWInputStream.java`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Action:** Fix the integer overflow issue in `[0m[1;35minitializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint maxCodeSize, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint memoryLimitInKiB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m[1;36m210[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m214[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Replace lines [0m[1;36m211[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m214[0m[39m:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmemoryLimiKiB > [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Prevent integer overflow by checking maxCodeSize before shifting[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxCodeSize > [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"maxCodeSize "[0m[39m + maxCodeSize + [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[32m" would cause integer overflow. Maximum allowed is 30."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    final long maxTableSize = 1L << maxCodeSize;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Use long to prevent overflow[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    final long memoryUsageBytes = maxTableSize * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprefixes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcharacters[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39moutputStack[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    final long memoryUsageKiB = memoryUsageBytes >> [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmemoryUsageKiB > memoryLimiKiB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mMemoryLimitException[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmemoryUsageKiB, memoryLimiKiB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale:**[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds explicit check for maxCodeSize > [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m before bit shifting[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses `long` for `maxTableSize` calculation to prevent integer overflow[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Ensures memory calculation is accurate even for large maxCodeSize values[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Makes the [0m[32m"account for potential overflow"[0m[39m comment accurate[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Defense-in-depth: even if validation is missed elsewhere, memory limit checks [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill work correctly[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Tertiary Fix: Add Upper Bound Check in Single-Argument initializeTables[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/compressors/lzw/LZWInputStream.java`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Action:** Improve validation in `[0m[1;35minitializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint maxCodeSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m184[0m[39m:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Replace lines [0m[1;36m181[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m184[0m[39m:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxCodeSize < [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m || maxCodeSize > [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mgetCodeSize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > maxCodeSize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"maxCodeSize "[0m[39m + maxCodeSize + [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[32m" is out of bounds. Valid range is [0m[32m[[0m[32m8, 30[0m[32m][0m[32m and must be >= current code [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32msize."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale:**[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds explicit upper bound check [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxCodeSize > [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removes reliance on integer overflow side effect for validation[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Makes the validation intent clear and maintainable[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Provides consistent error messages[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Aligns with test expectations and practical memory constraints[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m:** Apply the primary fix in `ZCompressorInputStream.java` constructor[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is the most critical fix as it prevents the vulnerability at the entry [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoint[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add validation immediately after reading maxCodeSize from input[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensures all code paths are protected regardless of memory limit configuration[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m:** Apply the secondary fix in `[0m[1;35mLZWInputStream.initializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fix the integer overflow bug in memory calculation[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use long arithmetic to handle large maxCodeSize values correctly[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add pre-shift validation to catch overflow conditions[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m:** Apply the tertiary fix in `[0m[1;35mLZWInputStream.initializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add explicit upper bound check[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove dependency on overflow side effects[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Improve code clarity and maintainability[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is Optimal[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Multiple layers of validation ensure the vulnerability is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcaught even if one layer fails[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Doesn't modify the fuzzing harness or test code[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintains compatibility with valid Z format files [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxCodeSize in [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests will continue to pass[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory limit mechanism remains functional[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Addresses All Root Causes**:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Missing input validation → Added in ZCompressorInputStream[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inadequate bounds checking → Improved in both initializeTables methods[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Integer overflow → Fixed with long arithmetic and pre-shift validation[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No default memory limit → Protected by explicit validation regardless of limit[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Consistent with Test Expectations**:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test expects IllegalArgumentException for values < [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m and >= [0m[1;36m31[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fix enforces [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m range which is more restrictive but safer[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses same exception type [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as tests expect[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Production-Safe**:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Protects the Expander API and other high-level components[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Works regardless of CompressorStreamFactory configuration[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No performance impact [0m[1;39m([0m[39msimple range check[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Clear error messages for debugging[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Stricter Validation**: Files with maxCodeSize < [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m or > [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m will be rejected[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: These values are outside practical Z format specifications[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The test already expects these to be invalid[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Most real-world Z files use maxCodeSize in range [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m][0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Error Message Changes**: Applications catching IOException might see [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIllegalArgumentException instead[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: IllegalArgumentException extends RuntimeException, so existing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException catches won't be affected[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is the expected exception type per the test suite[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Provides clearer indication of invalid input vs I/O errors[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Backward Compatibility**: Some edge case files might become unsupported[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: These files would already fail with OOM or [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMemoryLimitException[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fix makes failures explicit and early rather than causing resource [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexhaustion[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Better security posture outweighs edge case compatibility[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe `UnshrinkingInputStream` class provides a reference implementation:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses constant `MAX_CODE_SIZE = [0m[1;36m13[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m34[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Checks against this limit before incrementing code size [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m102[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This pattern of explicit bounds checking should be applied to Z compression[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe test suite at `[0m[1;35mZCompressorInputStreamTest.testInvalidMaxCodeSize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` defines the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected behavior, which this fix implements.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[01/09/26 21:04:33][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=601328;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=538724;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Array Size Calculation**: Even with `maxCodeSize` of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, `maxTableSize = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m << [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m` equals [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m073[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m741[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m824[0m[39m entries, resulting in:[0m                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs after the validation but the OOM happens before this check is reached [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Input Validation at Entry Points**: Examine how `maxCodeSize` values are [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextracted from the compressed stream header in `ZCompressorInputStream` and whether[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand whether it's properly configured or enforced before array allocation occurs[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Default Code Size Handling**: Examine the `DEFAULT_CODE_SIZE` and how it [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelates to the maximum allowed values, as well as the interaction between initial [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode size and maximum code size[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Input Analysis**: Analyze the specific test case [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggers this behavior to understand what `maxCodeSize` value is being provided and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether it represents valid compressed data[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Order of Operations**: The validation checks need to occur before any memory [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation, but the current structure may allow `[0m[1;35minitializeTables[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to be called [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith parameters that pass validation but still cause excessive allocation[0m           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
